<book id="jpa-queryex">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>Java Persistence API: Query Exercise</title>
        <subtitle>Creating Queries with JPA</subtitle>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>This document provides exercises to create JPA Queries using JPA Query
                 Language, native SQL, and (future) the Criteria API.
            </para>
        </abstract>
    </bookinfo>
    <preface id="jpa-queryex-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>
        <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
            <listitem><para>To provide hands on experience</para>
                <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                    <listitem><para>Creating JPA queries</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Creating native SQL queries</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Performing bulk database updates with JPA queries</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Adding locks to JPA queries</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem><para>At the completion of this exercise, the student will be able to</para>
                <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                    <listitem><para>Create a JPAQL query</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Create a SQL query</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Set query parameters</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Set paging controls</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Register a named query</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Define a SqlRowSetMapping</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Perform a bulk database update using JPAQL and native SQL</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Set the lock mode for a query</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <note>
            <para>The primary purpose of this exercise is to provide coverage of the broader capabilities 
                of JPA queries. Although some JPAQL features are exposed, it does not yet provide 
                detailed coverage of the JPA query language or SQL. It is expected that JPAQL will be
                a future enhancement to what is currently covered.</para>
        </note>
    </preface>

